 MBOMBELA – Two SAPS officers were travelling in a sedan on the R40 between White River and Hazyview when the accident occurred at about 15:30. Spokesman for the Department of Community Safety, Security and Liaison, Moeti Mmusi, confirmed that it is believed that a truck hit their vehicle from behind, causing their vehicle to crash into another truck near Da Gama Dam.  Mmusi said the officers could not be named until their next of kin had been notified. ALSO SEE:  Decorated traffic officer dies The department sent their condolences to the police management team, the men’s colleagues and their families. He added that it was not clear what had caused the collision. Police are investigating the matter. ALSO READ: Passanger in BMW dies after collision on the R40